name: Natural Repetition
description:
Repetition in nature is a common sight, from schools of fish to forests of trees, patterns of leaves to spores on a mushroom. The important thing to notice with natural repetition is the presence of variation-John Lovett.
This is the 3rd piece in the GHETTO SCANS series. The name is due to the illustrations being scanned in on a brother printer I found on the side of the road. I think it adds to the rawness and overall flavour.
